Benelli's SuperNova Tactical embodies a modular design concept in a 12-gauge pump-action shotgun. At the heart of this pump gun is a lightweight steel skeleton framework over-molded with a high-tech polymer, making the SuperNova Tactical super-light, super-strong, and almost completely impervious to any weather condition. But the SuperNova Tactical isn't just tough on the outside. Dual-action bars and a two-lug rotary bolt head that locks up steel to steel inside the barrel ensures that the SuperNova Tactical is rock solid to the core and capable of handling everything from 2-3/4" light loads to 3-1/2" Magnums. 

This SuperNova Tactical comes with newly designed, military-style ghost-ring sights (the harder to find version, sold out just about everywhere). The rear sight is click-adjustable for both windage and elevation.  A magazine cut-off on the forearm allows for safe carry with a full magazine and empty chamber. The top of the SuperNova's receiver is drilled and tapped to accommodate easy attachment of military-style optics.


Benelli’s SuperNova Tactical is a modular concept pump action shotgun, that can be configured to fit any defense or tactical situation.  The ComforTech stock absorbs nearly 48% of felt recoil to dampen the recoil of heavy buck shot loads.  In addition to taming recoil, the ComforTech system minimizes barrel climb, putting you back on target twice as fast as other comparable shotguns.  For tight quarters when clearing buildings or in a patrol vehicle nothing beats the compact versatility of the SuperNova.

This Benelli Supernova Tactical (20155) is a pump action shotgun that fires the 12 gauge shell. title: For Sale:  Exc. WWII Springfield M1 Garand SA/GAW Stock 1943
postcontent: This is an excellent condition and all correct WWII Springfield Armory M1 Garand in .30-06. The serial number on this M1 is 1946863, which places its date of manufacture in September 1943. The receiver has 98%+ of its original gray-green parkerized finish. The barrel is also Springfield manufactured and is SA marked and dated "9-43," so it is the original barrel for this rifle. The bore is excellent with a mirror bore and it gauges at 0.5 at the muzzle and about 2.5 at the throat so it is simply superb. The gas hole is correctly parkerized and the majority of the original parkerized finish remains on the barrel. The Rear Sight has the correct Type 1C Elevation Knob with knurled knob and closed arrow heads, Type 2B Lock Bar and Type 2 Rear Sight Cover. The Bolt is a correct -12SA Springfield bolt with the majority of its original parkerized finish and with wear on the friction points. The Operating Rod is an original, uncut and correct Type 5 "D35382 6SA" rod in excellent condition. The Follower Rod is a correct Type 4 "short fork" ribbed and riveted. The Operating Rod Catch is a correct Type 2. The Follower Arm is a correct Type 4 with rounded shoulders. The Follower is a correct Type 2C marked "11" on the bottom. The Bullet Guide is a correct Type 3 forged and milled with the wide slot. The Trigger Housing is a correct Type 8, -12SA marked with the majority of its original parkerized finish remaining. The Trigger Guard is the correct Type 1G, milled, that is unmarked. The Trigger is a correct Type 2 with no tooling hole and "S" mark. The Hammer is a correct Type 2D, -5SA marked. The Hammer Spring Plunger is a correct Type I with no rims on the sides. The Hammer Spring Housing is a correct Type 2. The Safety is a correct Type 3B, -9SA marked with most of the original parkerized finish remaining. The Gas Cylinder is a correct Type 2C, unmarked, wide, that has been field painted over (this part is stainless and GIs found that it would not take a parkerized finish and would turn silvery bright and they would use all kinds of things to reduce glare and keep this part dark). The Gas Cylinder Lock is a correct Type I chamfered front face. The Gas Lock Screw is the correct Type I Single Slot. The Stock is a beautiful original Springfield Armory walnut stock marked with boxed SA/GAW and large Ordnance Escutcheon on the left side, a small Ordnance Escutcheon on the bottom of the pistol grip, and a sharp circle sans serif "P" firing proof mark. The hand guards are also excellent and the colors of all three blend nicely together. There are no cracks in any of the wood and it just has minimal dings and small scratches from use. The stock is simply gorgeous. This rifle comes with an original MILSCO marked Model 1907 Leather Sling, dated 1944, that is in excellent condition. The black has worn from the steel clips, but it is supple and still has both leather keepers. The butt trap compartment has an original WWII plastic Type 2 Oiler with hole in the pull through end, which is fairly commonly seen since the soldiers used to break the cap so the pull through could be inserted without having to unscrew the cap. This is a simply beautiful and all correct WWII Springfield Armory M1 Garand from the middle of the war. This rifle is C&R eligible.

postcontent:
Patriot Training and Consulting, LLC, provides its clients with much more than just the minimum requirements of concealed carry certification training. We do not waste time teaching subject matter you already know, and we do not accept just anyone willing to pay the fee on the firing line either.

If someone accused us of placing high standards on our clients, we would have to enter a plea of guilt. We require every student to pass a handgun safety and proficiency test before the class starts to ensure the safety of all of our clients.

Because all of our Concealed Carry-Handgun (CCH) instructors are Marine Veterans who possess Criminal Justice expertise, we know first-hand how best to prepare you for two of the worst fights you could be in; a gun fight in the private sector, and the legal fight that will surely follow.

Though we teach the state mandated materials, we spend the majority of time teaching and explaining what you must know about North Carolina concealed carry and use of force law. If what you are looking for is both a challenge of your handgun skills and an educational course that will teach you much more than the N.C. CCH curriculum requires, this is your course.

PLEASE NOTE: It is our opinion that a concealed carry handgun course is NOT the place/time to become proficient with handguns. Anyone seeking to obtain their CCH Permit should already be proficient with handguns. For those who would benefit, we also offer NRA Pistol Courses. If you attend one of our NRA Pistol Courses first, we will discount your tuition fee for the CCH Course.

Visit us at www.PatriotTAC.com and on Facebook:
